    plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150
else:
    plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 75

Principal Component Analysis¶

In [5]:
# Get principal components using scikitlearn
K = 5 # Number of principal components
pca = PCA(n_components = K)
pca.fit(X) #  Calculate the PCs and eigenvalues of the data matrix X

V = pd.DataFrame(data=pca.components_.T, columns=['PC1','PC2','PC3','PC4','PC5'], index=X.columns) # Principal components
print('Principal components:\n', V) 

lam = pca.explained_variance_ # eigenvalues
print('\n Eigenvalues/variance of the projections:\n', lam)

# Proportion of variance explained
Normalised_lam = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
print('\nProportion of variance explained:\n ',Normalised_lam)
plt.figure()
plt.bar(['PC1','PC2','PC3','PC4','PC5'], Normalised_lam)
plt.ylabel('Prop. Explained variance')

plt.figure()
plt.pie( Normalised_lam, labels = ['PC1','PC2','PC3','PC4','PC5']);
plt.title('Prop. Explained variance');

# Compute and plot the projections onto the PCs
Z_pca = pca.transform(X) # Projections on the PCs
crabs2 = pd.concat([pd.DataFrame(Z_pca, columns = ['PC1', 'PC2', 'PC3', 'PC4', 'PC5']),y], axis=1)   
print(crabs2.head())

# Load data
from sklearn import datasets

(X, y) = datasets.fetch_olivetti_faces(return_X_y=True)
n, p = X.shape
print('n=' + np.str(n) + ', p='+np.str(p))
# Center the data (both rows and columns here)
X -= X.mean(axis=0)
X -= X.mean(axis=1).reshape(n, -1)

ncomp = 9 # Number of components
pca = PCA(n_components = ncomp)
pca.fit(X)
Z_pca = pca.transform(X) # Projections onto the PCs
print(Z_pca.shape) #  Check the shapes are ok

# Plot Projections onto the first two PCs; colors correspond to different individuals
plt.figure()
sns.scatterplot(x=Z_pca[:,0], y=Z_pca[:,1], hue = y, legend=[])
plt.tight_layout()
plt.xlabel('Coordinate 1')
plt.ylabel('Coordinate 2')
if svfigs:

In [12]:
# Plot the first 9 eigenfaces (eigenvectors), and the original and reconstructed images for 6 different images, chosen to have the maximum projection to some PCs
id_images = [np.argmax((Z_pca[:,0])),np.argmax((Z_pca[:,8])), np.argmax(np.abs(Z_pca[:,1])), np.argmax(np.abs(Z_pca[:,3])), np.argmax(np.abs(Z_pca[:,4]))]

plt.figure(figsize=(2.*10,2.* len(id_images)))
plt.title('Original')

# Plot the original and reconstructed images (the code is very inefficient and recompute the PCA for each image and each nb of components)
for j, id_im in enumerate(id_images):
    plt.subplot(len(id_images)+1, 10, 10*j+1)
    if j==0:
        plt.title('Original')
    plt.imshow(X[id_im,:].reshape(64, 64), cmap=plt.cm.gray, vmin=X.min(),vmax=X.max())
    plt.xticks(())
    plt.yticks(())
    for i in np.arange(ncomp):
        plt.subplot(len(id_images)+1, 10, j*10 + i + 2)
        pca = PCA(n_components = i+1) # PCA with i+1 components
        pca.fit(X) # Fit the parameters
        Z_pca = pca.transform(X) # Find the projections
        image = pca.inverse_transform(Z_pca[id_im,:]) # Calculate the reconstructed image
        plt.imshow(image.reshape(64, 64), cmap=plt.cm.gray, vmin=X.min(),vmax=X.max()) # plot the reconstructed image
        plt.xticks(())
        plt.yticks(())

plt.subplot(len(id_images)+1, 10, len(id_images)*10+1)
plt.text(-0.1,0.5, r'Eigenfaces $\to$')
plt.axis('off')
plt.xticks(())
plt.yticks(())
for i in np.arange(9): # Plot the eigenfaces
    plt.subplot(len(id_images)+1, 10, len(id_images)*10 + i + 2)
    image = pca.components_[i,:]
    plt.imshow(image.reshape(64, 64), cmap=plt.cm.gray, vmin=pca.components_.min(),vmax=pca.components_.max())
    plt.xticks(())
    plt.yticks(())
    plt.title(str(i+1), y=-.5)
    
# Save
if svfigs:
    plt.savefig(svdir + 'olivettifaces_ef.png', bbox_inches = 'tight')
